WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.162
<i>Previously on Kyle XY:</i>

00:03.269 --> 00:04.634
What is it?

00:04.738 --> 00:06.672
It's you.

00:06.740 --> 00:09.004
1985?

00:09.075 --> 00:11.441
I found out his name.
The guy in the photo.

00:11.544 --> 00:13.273
Adam Baylin.

00:13.346 --> 00:16.042
Adam Baylin has been missing
for 20 years.

00:16.116 --> 00:19.483
You gotta stop asking questions.
Forget about the past.

00:19.552 --> 00:22.248
Because if you don't
they'll kill you, Kyle.

00:22.922 --> 00:26.688
781227 was scheduled
for termination two months ago.

00:26.793 --> 00:30.661
This company cannot afford to have
that subject loose in the outside world.

00:31.798 --> 00:33.891
- Kyle!
- It's all gonna be OK.

00:35.935 --> 00:38.870
I've got a great thing going,
and I'm not gonna ruin it.

00:38.938 --> 00:40.064
Great for you.

00:40.140 --> 00:42.370
Go out with Amanda,
tap Hilary on the side.

00:42.442 --> 00:45.878
I can't help feeling
that I've let you down.

00:45.945 --> 00:47.173
Let me down?

00:47.247 --> 00:50.182
You made me feel like I was your son.

00:50.250 --> 00:51.808
Noah, is that really you?

00:53.987 --> 00:55.147
Who are you?

00:56.056 --> 00:59.958
It's Mom.
We finally found you.

01:02.929 --> 01:07.491
The kids called from the car.
Apparently, he had a seizure.

01:07.600 --> 01:10.364
It's gonna be OK.
We're gonna figure this out.

01:10.437 --> 01:12.371
That's about what happened.

01:13.473 --> 01:15.441
It's all we've been talking about.

01:15.508 --> 01:19.410
<i>At a glance, anyone would believe
the Petersons and I were related.</i>

01:19.479 --> 01:22.209
<i>They'd say I had
her mouth and his chin.</i>

01:22.282 --> 01:25.410
<i>But I wanted more
than a passing resemblance.</i>

01:25.485 --> 01:27.851
<i>Instead of thinking
they could be my parents,</i>

01:27.921 --> 01:29.889
<i>I needed to feel that they were.</i>

01:29.956 --> 01:32.117
They look like nice people.

01:32.225 --> 01:34.284
What the hell kind of name is Noah?

01:34.360 --> 01:36.828
I can't believe you.
Kyle's getting hauled off.

01:36.896 --> 01:39.057
Can't you think
of something decent to say?

01:39.165 --> 01:43.261
It's not like I want him to go.
He doesn't even look like a Noah.

01:43.703 --> 01:46.604
Do you think they'll want
to take me home with them soon?

01:47.307 --> 01:48.604
Maybe.

01:50.610 --> 01:51.702
I don't know.

01:51.778 --> 01:54.611
We'd lived in Hong Kong
for two years when it happened.

01:54.681 --> 01:57.514
Five years ago Noah left for school
and never came home.

01:57.584 --> 02:02.078
We thought it was a kidnapping,
some sort of extortion scheme.

02:02.155 --> 02:05.784
- David's an executive for a bank.
- There was never a ransom call.

02:05.859 --> 02:08.157
There were no clues,
from the beginning.

02:08.228 --> 02:11.197
Still, we never stopped looking for him.

02:11.297 --> 02:13.765
We never stopped hoping.

02:13.833 --> 02:16.996
And finally, out of nowhere,

02:17.103 --> 02:19.435
a hit on a missing person Web site.

02:19.506 --> 02:23.465
We couldn't tell from the picture,
but after talking to the detective

02:23.576 --> 02:25.305
and now seeing him...

02:27.180 --> 02:29.944
I used to call him
my wandering wonder.

02:30.583 --> 02:33.211
Sharp, inquisitive.

02:33.286 --> 02:36.653
Studying everything, taking it all in.

02:37.357 --> 02:40.019
Kyle is... I'm sorry.

02:40.093 --> 02:43.221
- We're so used to calling him that.
- We understand.

02:43.296 --> 02:45.594
Kyle is special.

02:45.665 --> 02:48.190
And different in many ways.

02:48.268 --> 02:51.203
He was born with some physical defects.

02:51.271 --> 02:53.739
His organs weren't
all in the right place.

02:53.806 --> 02:56.366
Corrective surgeries
have made him as good as new,

02:56.476 --> 02:58.535
but without a bellybutton.

02:59.979 --> 03:03.415
- We have so many questions.
- So do we.

03:03.483 --> 03:05.212
Well, they'll have to wait.

03:05.285 --> 03:09.221
The hospital arranged some DNA tests
to verify paternity. In the meantime...

03:09.289 --> 03:12.520
We were told that Noah has no memory

03:12.592 --> 03:14.719
from the day before he was found.

03:14.794 --> 03:16.694
I put this photo album together.

03:16.763 --> 03:19.493
Thought it might jog some memories.

03:21.000 --> 03:27.074
